f:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Crisp is best suited for startups, small teams, SaaS products, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Intercom, meanwhile, shines for SaaS companies, startups, product led growth, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2015, Crisp describes itself as \"All-in-one messaging platform combining live chat, chatbot, and knowledge base.\" Intercom, established in 2011, positions itself as \"AI-first customer service platform with chatbot, inbox, and help center.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
10:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Intercom** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (9.0 vs 7.0). However, this does not mean Crisp is a poor choice — far from it. Crisp excels in its own right, particularly for startups and small teams.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value best-in-class ai chatbot (fin), go with Intercom. If generous free plan matters more to you, Crisp is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
